## 🗃️ Database Design (Firebase Firestore)

```
Firestore
├── universities/
│   └── {slug}/ → name, description, location, status, confidence_threshold
│
├── university_cms/
│   └── {entry_id}/ → university_id, section_id, title, content, metadata{}
│                      status (draft|pending|approved|rejected|pending_delete)
│                      is_deleted, embedding_vector[], version, priority
│                      created_by, updated_by, approved_by, timestamps
│
├── university_knowledge/
│   └── {id}/ → university_id, question, answer, category, embedding_vector[], verified
│
├── users/
│   └── {uid}/ → email, display_name, role, university_id, is_active, status
│                 hashed_password (bcrypt), created_at
│
├── cms_audit_logs/
│   └── {log_id}/ → entry_id, section_id, university_id, action, performed_by, timestamp
│
├── university_requests/
│   └── {id}/ → university_name, email, status (pending|approved|rejected)
│
├── query_logs/
│   └── {id}/ → university_id, query, response, confidence_score, category, timestamp
│
├── query_feedback/
│   └── {id}/ → query_id, rating, comment, university_id, timestamp
│
├── otp_codes/
│   └── {email::purpose}/ → otp, expires_at (TTL 10min)
│
└── otp_verified/
    └── {email::purpose}/ → verified_token, expires_at (TTL 15min)
```

